main event: A witness observed two bright glowing objects changing colors and moving rapidly over Byrdstown, Tennessee on April 7, 1967 around 8:15 PM.
interesting points: The objects disappeared after approximately 30 seconds.
The weather conditions were clear with no cloud cover.
No physical evidence was found and no other witnesses were located.
The case was deemed 'Unresolved' due to insufficient information to determine the nature of the observed objects.
A separate report from April 14, 1967 in Sparta, Tennessee described an object like a 'missile' that went behind a hill and disappeared.
sighted object: two bright glowing objects, changing colors, moving rapidly
